3089static void save_state_to_tss32(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt,
3090 struct tss_segment_32 *tss)
3091{
3092 /* CR3 and ldt selector are not saved intentionally */
3093 tss->eip = ctxt->_eip;
3094 tss->eflags = ctxt->eflags;
3095 tss->eax = reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RAX);
3096 tss->ecx = reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RCX);
3097 tss->edx = reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RDX);
3098 tss->ebx = reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RBX);
3099 tss->esp = reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RSP);
3100 tss->ebp = reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RBP);
3101 tss->esi = reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RSI);
3102 tss->edi = reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RDI);
3103
3104 tss->es = get_segment_selector(ctxt, VCPU_SREG_ES);
3105 tss->cs = get_segment_selector(ctxt, VCPU_SREG_CS);
3106 tss->ss = get_segment_selector(ctxt, VCPU_SREG_SS);
3107 tss->ds = get_segment_selector(ctxt, VCPU_SREG_DS);
3108 tss->fs = get_segment_selector(ctxt, VCPU_SREG_FS);
3109 tss->gs = get_segment_selector(ctxt, VCPU_SREG_GS);
3110}
3111
3112static int load_state_from_tss32(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt,
3113 struct tss_segment_32 *tss)
3114{
3115 int ret;
3116 u8 cpl;
3117
3118 if (ctxt->ops->set_cr(ctxt, 3, tss->cr3))
3119 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
3120 ctxt->_eip = tss->eip;
3121 ctxt->eflags = tss->eflags | 2;
3122
3123 /* General purpose registers */
3124 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RAX) = tss->eax;
3125 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RCX) = tss->ecx;
3126 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RDX) = tss->edx;
3127 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RBX) = tss->ebx;
3128 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RSP) = tss->esp;
3129 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RBP) = tss->ebp;
3130 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RSI) = tss->esi;
3131 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RDI) = tss->edi;
3132
3133 /*
3134 * SDM says that segment selectors are loaded before segment
3135 * descriptors. This is important because CPL checks will
3136 * use CS.RPL.
3137 */
3138 set_segment_selector(ctxt, tss->ldt_selector, VCPU_SREG_LDTR);
3139 set_segment_selector(ctxt, tss->es, VCPU_SREG_ES);
3140 set_segment_selector(ctxt, tss->cs, VCPU_SREG_CS);
3141 set_segment_selector(ctxt, tss->ss, VCPU_SREG_SS);
3142 set_segment_selector(ctxt, tss->ds, VCPU_SREG_DS);
3143 set_segment_selector(ctxt, tss->fs, VCPU_SREG_FS);
3144 set_segment_selector(ctxt, tss->gs, VCPU_SREG_GS);
3145
3146 /*
3147 * If we're switching between Protected Mode and VM86, we need to make
3148 * sure to update the mode before loading the segment descriptors so
3149 * that the selectors are interpreted correctly.
3150 */
3151 if (ctxt->eflags & X86_EFLAGS_VM) {
3152 ctxt->mode = X86EMUL_MODE_VM86;
3153 cpl = 3;
3154 } else {
3155 ctxt->mode = X86EMUL_MODE_PROT32;
3156 cpl = tss->cs & 3;
3157 }
3158
3159 /*
3160 * Now load segment descriptors. If fault happenes at this stage
3161 * it is handled in a context of new task
3162 */
3163 ret = __load_segment_descriptor(ctxt, tss->ldt_selector, VCPU_SREG_LDTR,
3164 cpl, X86_TRANSFER_TASK_SWITCH, NULL);
3165 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3166 return ret;
3167 ret = __load_segment_descriptor(ctxt, tss->es, VCPU_SREG_ES, cpl,
3168 X86_TRANSFER_TASK_SWITCH, NULL);
3169 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3170 return ret;
3171 ret = __load_segment_descriptor(ctxt, tss->cs, VCPU_SREG_CS, cpl,
3172 X86_TRANSFER_TASK_SWITCH, NULL);
3173 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3174 return ret;
3175 ret = __load_segment_descriptor(ctxt, tss->ss, VCPU_SREG_SS, cpl,
3176 X86_TRANSFER_TASK_SWITCH, NULL);
3177 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3178 return ret;
3179 ret = __load_segment_descriptor(ctxt, tss->ds, VCPU_SREG_DS, cpl,
3180 X86_TRANSFER_TASK_SWITCH, NULL);
3181 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3182 return ret;
3183 ret = __load_segment_descriptor(ctxt, tss->fs, VCPU_SREG_FS, cpl,
3184 X86_TRANSFER_TASK_SWITCH, NULL);
3185 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3186 return ret;
3187 ret = __load_segment_descriptor(ctxt, tss->gs, VCPU_SREG_GS, cpl,
3188 X86_TRANSFER_TASK_SWITCH, NULL);
3189
3190 return ret;
3191}
3192
3193static int task_switch_32(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt,
3194 u16 tss_selector, u16 old_tss_sel,
3195 ulong old_tss_base, struct desc_struct *new_desc)
3196{
3197 struct tss_segment_32 tss_seg;
3198 int ret;
3199 u32 new_tss_base = get_desc_base(new_desc);
3200 u32 eip_offset = offsetof(struct tss_segment_32, eip);
3201 u32 ldt_sel_offset = offsetof(struct tss_segment_32, ldt_selector);
3202
3203 ret = linear_read_system(ctxt, old_tss_base, &tss_seg, sizeof tss_seg);
3204 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3205 return ret;
3206
3207 save_state_to_tss32(ctxt, &tss_seg);
3208
3209 /* Only GP registers and segment selectors are saved */
3210 ret = linear_write_system(ctxt, old_tss_base + eip_offset, &tss_seg.eip,
3211 ldt_sel_offset - eip_offset);
3212 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3213 return ret;
3214
3215 ret = linear_read_system(ctxt, new_tss_base, &tss_seg, sizeof tss_seg);
3216 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3217 return ret;
3218
3219 if (old_tss_sel != 0xffff) {
3220 tss_seg.prev_task_link = old_tss_sel;
3221
3222 ret = linear_write_system(ctxt, new_tss_base,
3223 &tss_seg.prev_task_link,
3224 sizeof tss_seg.prev_task_link);
3225 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3226 return ret;
3227 }
3228
3229 return load_state_from_tss32(ctxt, &tss_seg);
3230}
3231
3232static int emulator_do_task_switch(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt,
3233 u16 tss_selector, int idt_index, int reason,
3234 bool has_error_code, u32 error_code)
3235{
3236 const struct x86_emulate_ops *ops = ctxt->ops;
3237 struct desc_struct curr_tss_desc, next_tss_desc;
3238 int ret;
3239 u16 old_tss_sel = get_segment_selector(ctxt, VCPU_SREG_TR);
3240 ulong old_tss_base =
3241 ops->get_cached_segment_base(ctxt, VCPU_SREG_TR);
3242 u32 desc_limit;
3243 ulong desc_addr, dr7;
3244
3245 /* FIXME: old_tss_base == ~0 ? */
3246
3247 ret = read_segment_descriptor(ctxt, tss_selector, &next_tss_desc, &desc_addr);
3248 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3249 return ret;
3250 ret = read_segment_descriptor(ctxt, old_tss_sel, &curr_tss_desc, &desc_addr);
3251 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3252 return ret;
3253
3254 /* FIXME: check that next_tss_desc is tss */
3255
3256 /*
3257 * Check privileges. The three cases are task switch caused by...
3258 *
3259 * 1. jmp/call/int to task gate: Check against DPL of the task gate
3260 * 2. Exception/IRQ/iret: No check is performed
3261 * 3. jmp/call to TSS/task-gate: No check is performed since the
3262 * hardware checks it before exiting.
3263 */
3264 if (reason == TASK_SWITCH_GATE) {
3265 if (idt_index != -1) {
3266 /* Software interrupts */
3267 struct desc_struct task_gate_desc;
3268 int dpl;
3269
3270 ret = read_interrupt_descriptor(ctxt, idt_index,
3271 &task_gate_desc);
3272 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3273 return ret;
3274
3275 dpl = task_gate_desc.dpl;
3276 if ((tss_selector & 3) > dpl || ops->cpl(ctxt) > dpl)
3277 return emulate_gp(ctxt, (idt_index << 3) | 0x2);
3278 }
3279 }
3280
3281 desc_limit = desc_limit_scaled(&next_tss_desc);
3282 if (!next_tss_desc.p ||
3283 ((desc_limit < 0x67 && (next_tss_desc.type & 8)) ||
3284 desc_limit < 0x2b)) {
3285 return emulate_ts(ctxt, tss_selector & 0xfffc);
3286 }
3287
3288 if (reason == TASK_SWITCH_IRET || reason == TASK_SWITCH_JMP) {
3289 curr_tss_desc.type &= ~(1 << 1); /* clear busy flag */
3290 write_segment_descriptor(ctxt, old_tss_sel, &curr_tss_desc);
3291 }
3292
3293 if (reason == TASK_SWITCH_IRET)
3294 ctxt->eflags = ctxt->eflags & ~X86_EFLAGS_NT;
3295
3296 /* set back link to prev task only if NT bit is set in eflags
3297 note that old_tss_sel is not used after this point */
3298 if (reason != TASK_SWITCH_CALL && reason != TASK_SWITCH_GATE)
3299 old_tss_sel = 0xffff;
3300
3301 if (next_tss_desc.type & 8)
3302 ret = task_switch_32(ctxt, tss_selector, old_tss_sel,
3303 old_tss_base, &next_tss_desc);
3304 else
3305 ret = task_switch_16(ctxt, tss_selector, old_tss_sel,
3306 old_tss_base, &next_tss_desc);
3307 if (ret != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3308 return ret;
3309
3310 if (reason == TASK_SWITCH_CALL || reason == TASK_SWITCH_GATE)
3311 ctxt->eflags = ctxt->eflags | X86_EFLAGS_NT;
3312
3313 if (reason != TASK_SWITCH_IRET) {
3314 next_tss_desc.type |= (1 << 1); /* set busy flag */
3315 write_segment_descriptor(ctxt, tss_selector, &next_tss_desc);
3316 }
3317
3318 ops->set_cr(ctxt, 0, ops->get_cr(ctxt, 0) | X86_CR0_TS);
3319 ops->set_segment(ctxt, tss_selector, &next_tss_desc, 0, VCPU_SREG_TR);
3320
3321 if (has_error_code) {
3322 ctxt->op_bytes = ctxt->ad_bytes = (next_tss_desc.type & 8) ? 4 : 2;
3323 ctxt->lock_prefix = 0;
3324 ctxt->src.val = (unsigned long) error_code;
3325 ret = em_push(ctxt);
3326 }
3327
3328 ops->get_dr(ctxt, 7, &dr7);
3329 ops->set_dr(ctxt, 7, dr7 & ~(DR_LOCAL_ENABLE_MASK | DR_LOCAL_SLOWDOWN));
3330
3331 return ret;
3332}
3333
3334int emulator_task_switch(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt,
3335 u16 tss_selector, int idt_index, int reason,
3336 bool has_error_code, u32 error_code)
3337{
3338 int rc;
3339
3340 invalidate_registers(ctxt);
3341 ctxt->_eip = ctxt->eip;
3342 ctxt->dst.type = OP_NONE;
3343
3344 rc = emulator_do_task_switch(ctxt, tss_selector, idt_index, reason,
3345 has_error_code, error_code);
3346
3347 if (rc == X86EMUL_CONTINUE) {
3348 ctxt->eip = ctxt->_eip;
3349 writeback_registers(ctxt);
3350 }
3351
3352 return (rc == X86EMUL_UNHANDLEABLE) ? EMULATION_FAILED : EMULATION_OK;
3353}

3355static void string_addr_inc(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt, int reg,
3356 struct operand *op)
3357{
3358 int df = (ctxt->eflags & X86_EFLAGS_DF) ? -op->count : op->count;
3359
3360 register_address_increment(ctxt, reg, df * op->bytes);
3361 op->addr.mem.ea = register_address(ctxt, reg);
3362}
3363
3364static int em_das(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3365{
3366 u8 al, old_al;
3367 bool af, cf, old_cf;
3368
3369 cf = ctxt->eflags & X86_EFLAGS_CF;
3370 al = ctxt->dst.val;
3371
3372 old_al = al;
3373 old_cf = cf;
3374 cf = false;
3375 af = ctxt->eflags & X86_EFLAGS_AF;
3376 if ((al & 0x0f) > 9 || af) {
3377 al -= 6;
3378 cf = old_cf | (al >= 250);
3379 af = true;
3380 } else {
3381 af = false;
3382 }
3383 if (old_al > 0x99 || old_cf) {
3384 al -= 0x60;
3385 cf = true;
3386 }
3387
3388 ctxt->dst.val = al;
3389 /* Set PF, ZF, SF */
3390 ctxt->src.type = OP_IMM;
3391 ctxt->src.val = 0;
3392 ctxt->src.bytes = 1;
3393 fastop(ctxt, em_or);
3394 ctxt->eflags &= ~(X86_EFLAGS_AF | X86_EFLAGS_CF);
3395 if (cf)
3396 ctxt->eflags |= X86_EFLAGS_CF;
3397 if (af)
3398 ctxt->eflags |= X86_EFLAGS_AF;
3399 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3400}
3401
3402static int em_aam(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3403{
3404 u8 al, ah;
3405
3406 if (ctxt->src.val == 0)
3407 return emulate_de(ctxt);
3408
3409 al = ctxt->dst.val & 0xff;
3410 ah = al / ctxt->src.val;
3411 al %= ctxt->src.val;
3412
3413 ctxt->dst.val = (ctxt->dst.val & 0xffff0000) | al | (ah << 8);
3414
3415 /* Set PF, ZF, SF */
3416 ctxt->src.type = OP_IMM;
3417 ctxt->src.val = 0;
3418 ctxt->src.bytes = 1;
3419 fastop(ctxt, em_or);
3420
3421 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3422}
3423
3424static int em_aad(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3425{
3426 u8 al = ctxt->dst.val & 0xff;
3427 u8 ah = (ctxt->dst.val >> 8) & 0xff;
3428
3429 al = (al + (ah * ctxt->src.val)) & 0xff;
3430
3431 ctxt->dst.val = (ctxt->dst.val & 0xffff0000) | al;
3432
3433 /* Set PF, ZF, SF */
3434 ctxt->src.type = OP_IMM;
3435 ctxt->src.val = 0;
3436 ctxt->src.bytes = 1;
3437 fastop(ctxt, em_or);
3438
3439 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3440}

3442static int em_call(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3443{
3444 int rc;
3445 long rel = ctxt->src.val;
3446
3447 ctxt->src.val = (unsigned long)ctxt->_eip;
3448 rc = jmp_rel(ctxt, rel);
3449 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3450 return rc;
3451 return em_push(ctxt);
3452}
3453
3454static int em_call_far(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3455{
3456 u16 sel, old_cs;
3457 ulong old_eip;
3458 int rc;
3459 struct desc_struct old_desc, new_desc;
3460 const struct x86_emulate_ops *ops = ctxt->ops;
3461 int cpl = ctxt->ops->cpl(ctxt);
3462 enum x86emul_mode prev_mode = ctxt->mode;
3463
3464 old_eip = ctxt->_eip;
3465 ops->get_segment(ctxt, &old_cs, &old_desc, NULL, VCPU_SREG_CS);
3466
3467 memcpy(&sel, ctxt->src.valptr + ctxt->op_bytes, 2);
3468 rc = __load_segment_descriptor(ctxt, sel, VCPU_SREG_CS, cpl,
3469 X86_TRANSFER_CALL_JMP, &new_desc);
3470 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3471 return rc;
3472
3473 rc = assign_eip_far(ctxt, ctxt->src.val, &new_desc);
3474 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3475 goto fail;
3476
3477 ctxt->src.val = old_cs;
3478 rc = em_push(ctxt);
3479 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3480 goto fail;
3481
3482 ctxt->src.val = old_eip;
3483 rc = em_push(ctxt);
3484 /* If we failed, we tainted the memory, but the very least we should
3485 restore cs */
3486 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE) {
3487 pr_warn_once("faulting far call emulation tainted memory\n");
3488 goto fail;
3489 }
3490 return rc;
3491fail:
3492 ops->set_segment(ctxt, old_cs, &old_desc, 0, VCPU_SREG_CS);
3493 ctxt->mode = prev_mode;
3494 return rc;
3495
3496}

3498static int em_ret_near_imm(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3499{
3500 int rc;
3501 unsigned long eip;
3502
3503 rc = emulate_pop(ctxt, &eip, ctxt->op_bytes);
3504 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)

3506 rc = assign_eip_near(ctxt, eip);

3562static int em_mov(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3563{
3564 memcpy(ctxt->dst.valptr, ctxt->src.valptr, sizeof(ctxt->src.valptr));
3565 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;

3567
3568#define FFL(x) bit(X86_FEATURE_##x)
3569
3570static int em_movbe(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3571{
3572 u32 ebx, ecx, edx, eax = 1;
3573 u16 tmp;
3574
3575 /*
3576 * Check MOVBE is set in the guest-visible CPUID leaf.
3577 */
3578 ctxt->ops->get_cpuid(ctxt, &eax, &ebx, &ecx, &edx, false);
3579 if (!(ecx & FFL(MOVBE)))
3580 return emulate_ud(ctxt);
3581
3582 switch (ctxt->op_bytes) {
3583 case 2:
3584 /*
3585 * From MOVBE definition: "...When the operand size is 16 bits,
3586 * the upper word of the destination register remains unchanged
3587 * ..."
3588 *
3589 * Both casting ->valptr and ->val to u16 breaks strict aliasing
3590 * rules so we have to do the operation almost per hand.
3591 */
3592 tmp = (u16)ctxt->src.val;
3593 ctxt->dst.val &= ~0xffffUL;
3594 ctxt->dst.val |= (unsigned long)swab16(tmp);
3595 break;
3596 case 4:
3597 ctxt->dst.val = swab32((u32)ctxt->src.val);
3598 break;
3599 case 8:
3600 ctxt->dst.val = swab64(ctxt->src.val);
3601 break;
3602 default:
3603 BUG();
3604 }
3605 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3606}
3607
3608static int em_cr_write(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3609{
3610 if (ctxt->ops->set_cr(ctxt, ctxt->modrm_reg, ctxt->src.val))
3611 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
3612
3613 /* Disable writeback. */
3614 ctxt->dst.type = OP_NONE;
3615 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3616}
3617
3618static int em_dr_write(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3619{
3620 unsigned long val;
3621
3622 if (ctxt->mode == X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64)
3623 val = ctxt->src.val & ~0ULL;
3624 else
3625 val = ctxt->src.val & ~0U;
3626
3627 /* #UD condition is already handled. */
3628 if (ctxt->ops->set_dr(ctxt, ctxt->modrm_reg, val) < 0)
3629 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
3630
3631 /* Disable writeback. */
3632 ctxt->dst.type = OP_NONE;
3633 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3634}
3635
3636static int em_wrmsr(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3637{
3638 u64 msr_data;
3639
3640 msr_data = (u32)reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RAX)
3641 | ((u64)reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RDX) << 32);
3642 if (ctxt->ops->set_msr(ctxt, reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RCX), msr_data))
3643 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
3644
3645 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3646}
3647
3648static int em_rdmsr(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3649{
3650 u64 msr_data;
3651
3652 if (ctxt->ops->get_msr(ctxt, reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RCX), &msr_data))
3653 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
3654
3655 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RAX) = (u32)msr_data;
3656 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RDX) = msr_data >> 32;
3657 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3658}

3660static int em_mov_rm_sreg(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3661{
3662 if (ctxt->modrm_reg > VCPU_SREG_GS)
3663 return emulate_ud(ctxt);
3664
3665 ctxt->dst.val = get_segment_selector(ctxt, ctxt->modrm_reg);
3666 if (ctxt->dst.bytes == 4 && ctxt->dst.type == OP_MEM)
3667 ctxt->dst.bytes = 2;
3668 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3669}

3671static int em_mov_sreg_rm(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)

3741static int emulate_store_desc_ptr(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt,
3742 void (*get)(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt,
3743 struct desc_ptr *ptr))
3744{
3745 struct desc_ptr desc_ptr;
3746
3747 if (ctxt->mode == X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64)
3748 ctxt->op_bytes = 8;
3749 get(ctxt, &desc_ptr);
3750 if (ctxt->op_bytes == 2) {
3751 ctxt->op_bytes = 4;
3752 desc_ptr.address &= 0x00ffffff;
3753 }
3754 /* Disable writeback. */
3755 ctxt->dst.type = OP_NONE;
3756 return segmented_write_std(ctxt, ctxt->dst.addr.mem,
3757 &desc_ptr, 2 + ctxt->op_bytes);
3758}

3770static int em_lgdt_lidt(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt, bool lgdt)
3771{
3772 struct desc_ptr desc_ptr;
3773 int rc;
3774
3775 if (ctxt->mode == X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64)
3776 ctxt->op_bytes = 8;
3777 rc = read_descriptor(ctxt, ctxt->src.addr.mem,
3778 &desc_ptr.size, &desc_ptr.address,
3779 ctxt->op_bytes);
3780 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
3781 return rc;
3782 if (ctxt->mode == X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64 &&
3783 emul_is_noncanonical_address(desc_ptr.address, ctxt))
3784 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
3785 if (lgdt)
3786 ctxt->ops->set_gdt(ctxt, &desc_ptr);
3787 else
3788 ctxt->ops->set_idt(ctxt, &desc_ptr);
3789 /* Disable writeback. */
3790 ctxt->dst.type = OP_NONE;
3791 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3792}

3820static int em_loop(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3821{
3822 int rc = X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3823
3824 register_address_increment(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RCX, -1);
3825 if ((address_mask(ctxt, reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RCX)) != 0) &&
3826 (ctxt->b == 0xe2 || test_cc(ctxt->b ^ 0x5, ctxt->eflags)))
3827 rc = jmp_rel(ctxt, ctxt->src.val);
3828
3829 return rc;
3830}

3837 rc = jmp_rel(ctxt, ctxt->src.val);
3838
3839 return rc;

3879static int em_cpuid(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3880{
3881 u32 eax, ebx, ecx, edx;
3882 u64 msr = 0;
3883
3884 ctxt->ops->get_msr(ctxt, MSR_MISC_FEATURES_ENABLES, &msr);
3885 if (msr & MSR_MISC_FEATURES_ENABLES_CPUID_FAULT &&
3886 ctxt->ops->cpl(ctxt)) {
3887 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
3888 }
3889
3890 eax = reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RAX);
3891 ecx = reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RCX);
3892 ctxt->ops->get_cpuid(ctxt, &eax, &ebx, &ecx, &edx, true);
3893 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RAX) = eax;
3894 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RBX) = ebx;
3895 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RCX) = ecx;
3896 *reg_write(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RDX) = edx;
3897 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3898}

3900static int em_sahf(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3901{
3902 u32 flags;
3903
3904 flags = X86_EFLAGS_CF | X86_EFLAGS_PF | X86_EFLAGS_AF | X86_EFLAGS_ZF |
3905 X86_EFLAGS_SF;
3906 flags &= *reg_rmw(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RAX) >> 8;
3907
3908 ctxt->eflags &= ~0xffUL;
3909 ctxt->eflags |= flags | X86_EFLAGS_FIXED;
3910 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3911}

3916 *reg_rmw(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RAX) |= (ctxt->eflags & 0xff) << 8;
3917 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3918}

3946
3947static int check_fxsr(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3948{
3949 u32 eax = 1, ebx, ecx = 0, edx;
3950
3951 ctxt->ops->get_cpuid(ctxt, &eax, &ebx, &ecx, &edx, false);
3952 if (!(edx & FFL(FXSR)))
3953 return emulate_ud(ctxt);
3954
3955 if (ctxt->ops->get_cr(ctxt, 0) & (X86_CR0_TS | X86_CR0_EM))
3956 return emulate_nm(ctxt);
3957
3958 /*
3959 * Don't emulate a case that should never be hit, instead of working
3960 * around a lack of fxsave64/fxrstor64 on old compilers.
3961 */
3962 if (ctxt->mode >= X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64)
3963 return X86EMUL_UNHANDLEABLE;
3964
3965 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
3966}
3967
3968/*
3969 * Hardware doesn't save and restore XMM 0-7 without CR4.OSFXSR, but does save
3970 * and restore MXCSR.
3971 */
3972static size_t __fxstate_size(int nregs)
3973{
3974 return offsetof(struct fxregs_state, xmm_space[0]) + nregs * 16;
3975}
3976
3977static inline size_t fxstate_size(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
3978{
3979 bool cr4_osfxsr;
3980 if (ctxt->mode == X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64)
3981 return __fxstate_size(16);
3982
3983 cr4_osfxsr = ctxt->ops->get_cr(ctxt, 4) & X86_CR4_OSFXSR;
3984 return __fxstate_size(cr4_osfxsr ? 8 : 0);
3985}
3986
3987/*
3988 * FXSAVE and FXRSTOR have 4 different formats depending on execution mode,
3989 * 1) 16 bit mode
3990 * 2) 32 bit mode
3991 * - like (1), but FIP and FDP (foo) are only 16 bit. At least Intel CPUs
3992 * preserve whole 32 bit values, though, so (1) and (2) are the same wrt.
3993 * save and restore
3994 * 3) 64-bit mode with REX.W prefix
3995 * - like (2), but XMM 8-15 are being saved and restored
3996 * 4) 64-bit mode without REX.W prefix
3997 * - like (3), but FIP and FDP are 64 bit
3998 *
3999 * Emulation uses (3) for (1) and (2) and preserves XMM 8-15 to reach the
4000 * desired result. (4) is not emulated.
4001 *
4002 * Note: Guest and host CPUID.(EAX=07H,ECX=0H):EBX[bit 13] (deprecate FPU CS
4003 * and FPU DS) should match.
4004 */
4005static int em_fxsave(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4006{
4007 struct fxregs_state fx_state;
4008 int rc;
4009
4010 rc = check_fxsr(ctxt);
4011 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
4012 return rc;
4013
4014 ctxt->ops->get_fpu(ctxt);
4015
4016 rc = asm_safe("fxsave %[fx]", , [fx] "+m"(fx_state));
4017
4018 ctxt->ops->put_fpu(ctxt);
4019
4020 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
4021 return rc;
4022
4023 return segmented_write_std(ctxt, ctxt->memop.addr.mem, &fx_state,
4024 fxstate_size(ctxt));
4025}
4026
4027/*
4028 * FXRSTOR might restore XMM registers not provided by the guest. Fill
4029 * in the host registers (via FXSAVE) instead, so they won't be modified.
4030 * (preemption has to stay disabled until FXRSTOR).
4031 *
4032 * Use noinline to keep the stack for other functions called by callers small.
4033 */
4034static noinline int fxregs_fixup(struct fxregs_state *fx_state,
4035 const size_t used_size)
4036{
4037 struct fxregs_state fx_tmp;
4038 int rc;
4039
4040 rc = asm_safe("fxsave %[fx]", , [fx] "+m"(fx_tmp));
4041 memcpy((void *)fx_state + used_size, (void *)&fx_tmp + used_size,
4042 __fxstate_size(16) - used_size);
4043
4044 return rc;
4045}
4046
4047static int em_fxrstor(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4048{
4049 struct fxregs_state fx_state;
4050 int rc;
4051 size_t size;
4052
4053 rc = check_fxsr(ctxt);
4054 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
4055 return rc;
4056
4057 size = fxstate_size(ctxt);
4058 rc = segmented_read_std(ctxt, ctxt->memop.addr.mem, &fx_state, size);
4059 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
4060 return rc;
4061
4062 ctxt->ops->get_fpu(ctxt);
4063
4064 if (size < __fxstate_size(16)) {
4065 rc = fxregs_fixup(&fx_state, size);
4066 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
4067 goto out;
4068 }
4069
4070 if (fx_state.mxcsr >> 16) {
4071 rc = emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
4072 goto out;
4073 }
4074
4075 if (rc == X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
4076 rc = asm_safe("fxrstor %[fx]", : [fx] "m"(fx_state));
4077
4078out:
4079 ctxt->ops->put_fpu(ctxt);
4080
4081 return rc;
4082}

4084static bool valid_cr(int nr)
4085{
4086 switch (nr) {
4087 case 0:
4088 case 2 ... 4:
4089 case 8:
4090 return true;
4091 default:
4092 return false;
4093 }
4094}

4096static int check_cr_read(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4097{
4098 if (!valid_cr(ctxt->modrm_reg))
4099 return emulate_ud(ctxt);
4100
4101 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
4102}
4103
4104static int check_cr_write(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4105{
4106 u64 new_val = ctxt->src.val64;
4107 int cr = ctxt->modrm_reg;
4108 u64 efer = 0;
4109
4110 static u64 cr_reserved_bits[] = {
4111 0xffffffff00000000ULL,
4112 0, 0, 0, /* CR3 checked later */
4113 CR4_RESERVED_BITS,
4114 0, 0, 0,
4115 CR8_RESERVED_BITS,
4116 };
4117
4118 if (!valid_cr(cr))
4119 return emulate_ud(ctxt);
4120
4121 if (new_val & cr_reserved_bits[cr])
4122 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
4123
4124 switch (cr) {
4125 case 0: {
4126 u64 cr4;
4127 if (((new_val & X86_CR0_PG) && !(new_val & X86_CR0_PE)) ||
4128 ((new_val & X86_CR0_NW) && !(new_val & X86_CR0_CD)))
4129 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
4130
4131 cr4 = ctxt->ops->get_cr(ctxt, 4);
4132 ctxt->ops->get_msr(ctxt, MSR_EFER, &efer);
4133
4134 if ((new_val & X86_CR0_PG) && (efer & EFER_LME) &&
4135 !(cr4 & X86_CR4_PAE))
4136 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
4137
4138 break;
4139 }
4140 case 3: {
4141 u64 rsvd = 0;
4142
4143 ctxt->ops->get_msr(ctxt, MSR_EFER, &efer);
4144 if (efer & EFER_LMA) {
4145 u64 maxphyaddr;
4146 u32 eax, ebx, ecx, edx;
4147
4148 eax = 0x80000008;
4149 ecx = 0;
4150 if (ctxt->ops->get_cpuid(ctxt, &eax, &ebx, &ecx,
4151 &edx, false))
4152 maxphyaddr = eax & 0xff;
4153 else
4154 maxphyaddr = 36;
4155 rsvd = rsvd_bits(maxphyaddr, 63);
4156 if (ctxt->ops->get_cr(ctxt, 4) & X86_CR4_PCIDE)
4157 rsvd &= ~CR3_PCID_INVD;
4158 }
4159
4160 if (new_val & rsvd)
4161 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
4162
4163 break;
4164 }
4165 case 4: {
4166 ctxt->ops->get_msr(ctxt, MSR_EFER, &efer);
4167
4168 if ((efer & EFER_LMA) && !(new_val & X86_CR4_PAE))
4169 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
4170
4171 break;
4172 }
4173 }
4174
4175 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
4176}
4177
4178static int check_dr7_gd(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4179{
4180 unsigned long dr7;
4181
4182 ctxt->ops->get_dr(ctxt, 7, &dr7);
4183
4184 /* Check if DR7.Global_Enable is set */
4185 return dr7 & (1 << 13);
4186}
4187
4188static int check_dr_read(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4189{
4190 int dr = ctxt->modrm_reg;
4191 u64 cr4;
4192
4193 if (dr > 7)
4194 return emulate_ud(ctxt);
4195
4196 cr4 = ctxt->ops->get_cr(ctxt, 4);
4197 if ((cr4 & X86_CR4_DE) && (dr == 4 || dr == 5))
4198 return emulate_ud(ctxt);
4199
4200 if (check_dr7_gd(ctxt)) {
4201 ulong dr6;
4202
4203 ctxt->ops->get_dr(ctxt, 6, &dr6);
4204 dr6 &= ~15;
4205 dr6 |= DR6_BD | DR6_RTM;
4206 ctxt->ops->set_dr(ctxt, 6, dr6);
4207 return emulate_db(ctxt);
4208 }
4209
4210 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
4211}
4212
4213static int check_dr_write(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4214{
4215 u64 new_val = ctxt->src.val64;
4216 int dr = ctxt->modrm_reg;
4217
4218 if ((dr == 6 || dr == 7) && (new_val & 0xffffffff00000000ULL))
4219 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
4220
4221 return check_dr_read(ctxt);
4222}

4224static int check_svme(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4225{
4226 u64 efer = 0;
4227
4228 ctxt->ops->get_msr(ctxt, MSR_EFER, &efer);
4229
4230 if (!(efer & EFER_SVME))
4231 return emulate_ud(ctxt);
4232
4233 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
4234}
4235
4236static int check_svme_pa(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4237{
4238 u64 rax = reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RAX);
4239
4240 /* Valid physical address? */
4241 if (rax & 0xffff000000000000ULL)
4242 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
4243
4244 return check_svme(ctxt);
4245}
4246
4247static int check_rdtsc(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4248{
4249 u64 cr4 = ctxt->ops->get_cr(ctxt, 4);
4250
4251 if (cr4 & X86_CR4_TSD && ctxt->ops->cpl(ctxt))
4252 return emulate_ud(ctxt);
4253
4254 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
4255}
4256
4257static int check_rdpmc(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4258{
4259 u64 cr4 = ctxt->ops->get_cr(ctxt, 4);
4260 u64 rcx = reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RCX);
4261
4262 if ((!(cr4 & X86_CR4_PCE) && ctxt->ops->cpl(ctxt)) ||
4263 ctxt->ops->check_pmc(ctxt, rcx))
4264 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
4265
4266 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
4267}
4268
4269static int check_perm_in(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4270{
4271 ctxt->dst.bytes = min(ctxt->dst.bytes, 4u);
4272 if (!emulator_io_permited(ctxt, ctxt->src.val, ctxt->dst.bytes))
4273 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
4274
4275 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
4276}
4277
4278static int check_perm_out(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4279{
4280 ctxt->src.bytes = min(ctxt->src.bytes, 4u);
4281 if (!emulator_io_permited(ctxt, ctxt->dst.val, ctxt->src.bytes))
4282 return emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
4283
4284 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
4285}

4287#define D(_y) { .flags = (_y) }

4298#define I(_f, _e) { .flags = (_f), .u.execute = (_e) }
4299#define F(_f, _e) { .flags = (_f) | Fastop, .u.fastop = (_e) }

4301 { .flags = (_f)|Intercept, .u.execute = (_e), .intercept = x86_intercept_##_i }
4302#define IIP(_f, _e, _i, _p) \
4303 { .flags = (_f)|Intercept|CheckPerm, .u.execute = (_e), \
4304 .intercept = x86_intercept_##_i, .check_perm = (_p) }
4305#define GP(_f, _g) { .flags = ((_f) | Prefix), .u.gprefix = (_g) }

4811static unsigned imm_size(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
4812{
4813 unsigned size;
4814
4815 size = (ctxt->d & ByteOp) ? 1 : ctxt->op_bytes;
4816 if (size == 8)
4817 size = 4;
4818 return size;
4819}
4820
4821static int decode_imm(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt, struct operand *op,
4822 unsigned size, bool sign_extension)
4823{
4824 int rc = X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
4825
4826 op->type = OP_IMM;
4827 op->bytes = size;
4828 op->addr.mem.ea = ctxt->_eip;
4829 /* NB. Immediates are sign-extended as necessary. */
4830 switch (op->bytes) {
4831 case 1:
4832 op->val = insn_fetch(s8, ctxt);
4833 break;
4834 case 2:
4835 op->val = insn_fetch(s16, ctxt);
4836 break;
4837 case 4:
4838 op->val = insn_fetch(s32, ctxt);
4839 break;
4840 case 8:
4841 op->val = insn_fetch(s64, ctxt);
4842 break;
4843 }
4844 if (!sign_extension) {
4845 switch (op->bytes) {
4846 case 1:
4847 op->val &= 0xff;
4848 break;
4849 case 2:
4850 op->val &= 0xffff;
4851 break;
4852 case 4:
4853 op->val &= 0xffffffff;
4854 break;
4855 }
4856 }
4857done:
4858 return rc;
4859}
4860
4861static int decode_operand(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt, struct operand *op,
4862 unsigned d)
4863{
4864 int rc = X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
4865
4866 switch (d) {
4867 case OpReg:
4868 decode_register_operand(ctxt, op);
4869 break;
4870 case OpImmUByte:
4871 rc = decode_imm(ctxt, op, 1, false);
4872 break;
4873 case OpMem:
4874 ctxt->memop.bytes = (ctxt->d & ByteOp) ? 1 : ctxt->op_bytes;
4875 mem_common:
4876 *op = ctxt->memop;
4877 ctxt->memopp = op;
4878 if (ctxt->d & BitOp)
4879 fetch_bit_operand(ctxt);
4880 op->orig_val = op->val;
4881 break;
4882 case OpMem64:
4883 ctxt->memop.bytes = (ctxt->op_bytes == 8) ? 16 : 8;
4884 goto mem_common;
4885 case OpAcc:
4886 op->type = OP_REG;
4887 op->bytes = (ctxt->d & ByteOp) ? 1 : ctxt->op_bytes;
4888 op->addr.reg = reg_rmw(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RAX);
4889 fetch_register_operand(op);
4890 op->orig_val = op->val;
4891 break;
4892 case OpAccLo:
4893 op->type = OP_REG;
4894 op->bytes = (ctxt->d & ByteOp) ? 2 : ctxt->op_bytes;
4895 op->addr.reg = reg_rmw(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RAX);
4896 fetch_register_operand(op);
4897 op->orig_val = op->val;
4898 break;
4899 case OpAccHi:
4900 if (ctxt->d & ByteOp) {
4901 op->type = OP_NONE;
4902 break;
4903 }
4904 op->type = OP_REG;
4905 op->bytes = ctxt->op_bytes;
4906 op->addr.reg = reg_rmw(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RDX);
4907 fetch_register_operand(op);
4908 op->orig_val = op->val;
4909 break;
4910 case OpDI:
4911 op->type = OP_MEM;
4912 op->bytes = (ctxt->d & ByteOp) ? 1 : ctxt->op_bytes;
4913 op->addr.mem.ea =
4914 register_address(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RDI);
4915 op->addr.mem.seg = VCPU_SREG_ES;
4916 op->val = 0;
4917 op->count = 1;
4918 break;
4919 case OpDX:
4920 op->type = OP_REG;
4921 op->bytes = 2;
4922 op->addr.reg = reg_rmw(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RDX);
4923 fetch_register_operand(op);
4924 break;
4925 case OpCL:
4926 op->type = OP_IMM;
4927 op->bytes = 1;
4928 op->val = reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RCX) & 0xff;
4929 break;
4930 case OpImmByte:
4931 rc = decode_imm(ctxt, op, 1, true);
4932 break;
4933 case OpOne:
4934 op->type = OP_IMM;
4935 op->bytes = 1;
4936 op->val = 1;
4937 break;
4938 case OpImm:
4939 rc = decode_imm(ctxt, op, imm_size(ctxt), true);
4940 break;
4941 case OpImm64:
4942 rc = decode_imm(ctxt, op, ctxt->op_bytes, true);
4943 break;
4944 case OpMem8:
4945 ctxt->memop.bytes = 1;
4946 if (ctxt->memop.type == OP_REG) {
4947 ctxt->memop.addr.reg = decode_register(ctxt,
4948 ctxt->modrm_rm, true);
4949 fetch_register_operand(&ctxt->memop);
4950 }
4951 goto mem_common;
4952 case OpMem16:
4953 ctxt->memop.bytes = 2;
4954 goto mem_common;
4955 case OpMem32:
4956 ctxt->memop.bytes = 4;
4957 goto mem_common;
4958 case OpImmU16:
4959 rc = decode_imm(ctxt, op, 2, false);
4960 break;
4961 case OpImmU:
4962 rc = decode_imm(ctxt, op, imm_size(ctxt), false);
4963 break;
4964 case OpSI:
4965 op->type = OP_MEM;
4966 op->bytes = (ctxt->d & ByteOp) ? 1 : ctxt->op_bytes;
4967 op->addr.mem.ea =
4968 register_address(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RSI);
4969 op->addr.mem.seg = ctxt->seg_override;
4970 op->val = 0;
4971 op->count = 1;
4972 break;
4973 case OpXLat:
4974 op->type = OP_MEM;
4975 op->bytes = (ctxt->d & ByteOp) ? 1 : ctxt->op_bytes;
4976 op->addr.mem.ea =
4977 address_mask(ctxt,
4978 reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RBX) +
4979 (reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RAX) & 0xff));
4980 op->addr.mem.seg = ctxt->seg_override;
4981 op->val = 0;
4982 break;
4983 case OpImmFAddr:
4984 op->type = OP_IMM;
4985 op->addr.mem.ea = ctxt->_eip;
4986 op->bytes = ctxt->op_bytes + 2;
4987 insn_fetch_arr(op->valptr, op->bytes, ctxt);
4988 break;
4989 case OpMemFAddr:
4990 ctxt->memop.bytes = ctxt->op_bytes + 2;
4991 goto mem_common;
4992 case OpES:
4993 op->type = OP_IMM;
4994 op->val = VCPU_SREG_ES;
4995 break;
4996 case OpCS:
4997 op->type = OP_IMM;
4998 op->val = VCPU_SREG_CS;
4999 break;
5000 case OpSS:
5001 op->type = OP_IMM;
5002 op->val = VCPU_SREG_SS;
5003 break;
5004 case OpDS:
5005 op->type = OP_IMM;
5006 op->val = VCPU_SREG_DS;
5007 break;
5008 case OpFS:
5009 op->type = OP_IMM;
5010 op->val = VCPU_SREG_FS;
5011 break;
5012 case OpGS:
5013 op->type = OP_IMM;
5014 op->val = VCPU_SREG_GS;
5015 break;
5016 case OpImplicit:
5017 /* Special instructions do their own operand decoding. */
5018 default:
5019 op->type = OP_NONE; /* Disable writeback. */
5020 break;
5021 }
5022
5023done:
5024 return rc;
5025}
5026
5027int x86_decode_insn(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt, void *insn, int insn_len)
5028{
5029 int rc = X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
5030 int mode = ctxt->mode;
5031 int def_op_bytes, def_ad_bytes, goffset, simd_prefix;
5032 bool op_prefix = false;
5033 bool has_seg_override = false;
5034 struct opcode opcode;
5035 u16 dummy;
5036 struct desc_struct desc;
5037
5038 ctxt->memop.type = OP_NONE;
5039 ctxt->memopp = NULL;
5040 ctxt->_eip = ctxt->eip;
5041 ctxt->fetch.ptr = ctxt->fetch.data;
5042 ctxt->fetch.end = ctxt->fetch.data + insn_len;
5043 ctxt->opcode_len = 1;
5044 if (insn_len > 0)
5045 memcpy(ctxt->fetch.data, insn, insn_len);
5046 else {
5047 rc = __do_insn_fetch_bytes(ctxt, 1);
5048 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5049 return rc;
5050 }
5051
5052 switch (mode) {
5053 case X86EMUL_MODE_REAL:
5054 case X86EMUL_MODE_VM86:
5055 def_op_bytes = def_ad_bytes = 2;
5056 ctxt->ops->get_segment(ctxt, &dummy, &desc, NULL, VCPU_SREG_CS);
5057 if (desc.d)
5058 def_op_bytes = def_ad_bytes = 4;
5059 break;
5060 case X86EMUL_MODE_PROT16:
5061 def_op_bytes = def_ad_bytes = 2;
5062 break;
5063 case X86EMUL_MODE_PROT32:
5064 def_op_bytes = def_ad_bytes = 4;
5065 break;
5066#ifdef CONFIG_X86_64
5067 case X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64:
5068 def_op_bytes = 4;
5069 def_ad_bytes = 8;
5070 break;
5071#endif
5072 default:
5073 return EMULATION_FAILED;
5074 }
5075
5076 ctxt->op_bytes = def_op_bytes;
5077 ctxt->ad_bytes = def_ad_bytes;
5078
5079 /* Legacy prefixes. */
5080 for (;;) {
5081 switch (ctxt->b = insn_fetch(u8, ctxt)) {
5082 case 0x66: /* operand-size override */
5083 op_prefix = true;
5084 /* switch between 2/4 bytes */
5085 ctxt->op_bytes = def_op_bytes ^ 6;
5086 break;
5087 case 0x67: /* address-size override */
5088 if (mode == X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64)
5089 /* switch between 4/8 bytes */
5090 ctxt->ad_bytes = def_ad_bytes ^ 12;
5091 else
5092 /* switch between 2/4 bytes */
5093 ctxt->ad_bytes = def_ad_bytes ^ 6;
5094 break;
5095 case 0x26: /* ES override */
5096 case 0x2e: /* CS override */
5097 case 0x36: /* SS override */
5098 case 0x3e: /* DS override */
5099 has_seg_override = true;
5100 ctxt->seg_override = (ctxt->b >> 3) & 3;
5101 break;
5102 case 0x64: /* FS override */
5103 case 0x65: /* GS override */
5104 has_seg_override = true;
5105 ctxt->seg_override = ctxt->b & 7;
5106 break;
5107 case 0x40 ... 0x4f: /* REX */
5108 if (mode != X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64)
5109 goto done_prefixes;
5110 ctxt->rex_prefix = ctxt->b;
5111 continue;
5112 case 0xf0: /* LOCK */
5113 ctxt->lock_prefix = 1;
5114 break;
5115 case 0xf2: /* REPNE/REPNZ */
5116 case 0xf3: /* REP/REPE/REPZ */
5117 ctxt->rep_prefix = ctxt->b;
5118 break;
5119 default:
5120 goto done_prefixes;
5121 }
5122
5123 /* Any legacy prefix after a REX prefix nullifies its effect. */
5124
5125 ctxt->rex_prefix = 0;
5126 }
5127
5128done_prefixes:
5129
5130 /* REX prefix. */
5131 if (ctxt->rex_prefix & 8)
5132 ctxt->op_bytes = 8; /* REX.W */
5133
5134 /* Opcode byte(s). */
5135 opcode = opcode_table[ctxt->b];
5136 /* Two-byte opcode? */
5137 if (ctxt->b == 0x0f) {
5138 ctxt->opcode_len = 2;
5139 ctxt->b = insn_fetch(u8, ctxt);
5140 opcode = twobyte_table[ctxt->b];
5141
5142 /* 0F_38 opcode map */
5143 if (ctxt->b == 0x38) {
5144 ctxt->opcode_len = 3;
5145 ctxt->b = insn_fetch(u8, ctxt);
5146 opcode = opcode_map_0f_38[ctxt->b];
5147 }
5148 }
5149 ctxt->d = opcode.flags;
5150
5151 if (ctxt->d & ModRM)
5152 ctxt->modrm = insn_fetch(u8, ctxt);
5153
5154 /* vex-prefix instructions are not implemented */
5155 if (ctxt->opcode_len == 1 && (ctxt->b == 0xc5 || ctxt->b == 0xc4) &&
5156 (mode == X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64 || (ctxt->modrm & 0xc0) == 0xc0)) {
5157 ctxt->d = NotImpl;
5158 }
5159
5160 while (ctxt->d & GroupMask) {
5161 switch (ctxt->d & GroupMask) {
5162 case Group:
5163 goffset = (ctxt->modrm >> 3) & 7;
5164 opcode = opcode.u.group[goffset];
5165 break;
5166 case GroupDual:
5167 goffset = (ctxt->modrm >> 3) & 7;
5168 if ((ctxt->modrm >> 6) == 3)
5169 opcode = opcode.u.gdual->mod3[goffset];
5170 else
5171 opcode = opcode.u.gdual->mod012[goffset];
5172 break;
5173 case RMExt:
5174 goffset = ctxt->modrm & 7;
5175 opcode = opcode.u.group[goffset];
5176 break;
5177 case Prefix:
5178 if (ctxt->rep_prefix && op_prefix)
5179 return EMULATION_FAILED;
5180 simd_prefix = op_prefix ? 0x66 : ctxt->rep_prefix;
5181 switch (simd_prefix) {
5182 case 0x00: opcode = opcode.u.gprefix->pfx_no; break;
5183 case 0x66: opcode = opcode.u.gprefix->pfx_66; break;
5184 case 0xf2: opcode = opcode.u.gprefix->pfx_f2; break;
5185 case 0xf3: opcode = opcode.u.gprefix->pfx_f3; break;
5186 }
5187 break;
5188 case Escape:
5189 if (ctxt->modrm > 0xbf)
5190 opcode = opcode.u.esc->high[ctxt->modrm - 0xc0];
5191 else
5192 opcode = opcode.u.esc->op[(ctxt->modrm >> 3) & 7];
5193 break;
5194 case InstrDual:
5195 if ((ctxt->modrm >> 6) == 3)
5196 opcode = opcode.u.idual->mod3;
5197 else
5198 opcode = opcode.u.idual->mod012;
5199 break;
5200 case ModeDual:
5201 if (ctxt->mode == X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64)
5202 opcode = opcode.u.mdual->mode64;
5203 else
5204 opcode = opcode.u.mdual->mode32;
5205 break;
5206 default:
5207 return EMULATION_FAILED;
5208 }
5209
5210 ctxt->d &= ~(u64)GroupMask;
5211 ctxt->d |= opcode.flags;
5212 }
5213
5214 /* Unrecognised? */
5215 if (ctxt->d == 0)
5216 return EMULATION_FAILED;
5217
5218 ctxt->execute = opcode.u.execute;
5219
5220 if (unlikely(ctxt->ud) && likely(!(ctxt->d & EmulateOnUD)))
5221 return EMULATION_FAILED;
5222
5223 if (unlikely(ctxt->d &
5224 (NotImpl|Stack|Op3264|Sse|Mmx|Intercept|CheckPerm|NearBranch|
5225 No16))) {
5226 /*
5227 * These are copied unconditionally here, and checked unconditionally
5228 * in x86_emulate_insn.
5229 */
5230 ctxt->check_perm = opcode.check_perm;
5231 ctxt->intercept = opcode.intercept;
5232
5233 if (ctxt->d & NotImpl)
5234 return EMULATION_FAILED;
5235
5236 if (mode == X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64) {
5237 if (ctxt->op_bytes == 4 && (ctxt->d & Stack))
5238 ctxt->op_bytes = 8;
5239 else if (ctxt->d & NearBranch)
5240 ctxt->op_bytes = 8;
5241 }
5242
5243 if (ctxt->d & Op3264) {
5244 if (mode == X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64)
5245 ctxt->op_bytes = 8;
5246 else
5247 ctxt->op_bytes = 4;
5248 }
5249
5250 if ((ctxt->d & No16) && ctxt->op_bytes == 2)
5251 ctxt->op_bytes = 4;
5252
5253 if (ctxt->d & Sse)
5254 ctxt->op_bytes = 16;
5255 else if (ctxt->d & Mmx)
5256 ctxt->op_bytes = 8;
5257 }
5258
5259 /* ModRM and SIB bytes. */
5260 if (ctxt->d & ModRM) {
5261 rc = decode_modrm(ctxt, &ctxt->memop);
5262 if (!has_seg_override) {
5263 has_seg_override = true;
5264 ctxt->seg_override = ctxt->modrm_seg;
5265 }
5266 } else if (ctxt->d & MemAbs)
5267 rc = decode_abs(ctxt, &ctxt->memop);
5268 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5269 goto done;
5270
5271 if (!has_seg_override)
5272 ctxt->seg_override = VCPU_SREG_DS;
5273
5274 ctxt->memop.addr.mem.seg = ctxt->seg_override;
5275
5276 /*
5277 * Decode and fetch the source operand: register, memory
5278 * or immediate.
5279 */
5280 rc = decode_operand(ctxt, &ctxt->src, (ctxt->d >> SrcShift) & OpMask);
5281 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5282 goto done;
5283
5284 /*
5285 * Decode and fetch the second source operand: register, memory
5286 * or immediate.
5287 */
5288 rc = decode_operand(ctxt, &ctxt->src2, (ctxt->d >> Src2Shift) & OpMask);
5289 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5290 goto done;
5291
5292 /* Decode and fetch the destination operand: register or memory. */
5293 rc = decode_operand(ctxt, &ctxt->dst, (ctxt->d >> DstShift) & OpMask);
5294
5295 if (ctxt->rip_relative && likely(ctxt->memopp))
5296 ctxt->memopp->addr.mem.ea = address_mask(ctxt,
5297 ctxt->memopp->addr.mem.ea + ctxt->_eip);
5298
5299done:
5300 return (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE) ? EMULATION_FAILED : EMULATION_OK;
5301}
5302
5303bool x86_page_table_writing_insn(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
5304{
5305 return ctxt->d & PageTable;
5306}
5307
5308static bool string_insn_completed(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
5309{
5310 /* The second termination condition only applies for REPE
5311 * and REPNE. Test if the repeat string operation prefix is
5312 * REPE/REPZ or REPNE/REPNZ and if it's the case it tests the
5313 * corresponding termination condition according to:
5314 * - if REPE/REPZ and ZF = 0 then done
5315 * - if REPNE/REPNZ and ZF = 1 then done
5316 */
5317 if (((ctxt->b == 0xa6) || (ctxt->b == 0xa7) ||
5318 (ctxt->b == 0xae) || (ctxt->b == 0xaf))
5319 && (((ctxt->rep_prefix == REPE_PREFIX) &&
5320 ((ctxt->eflags & X86_EFLAGS_ZF) == 0))
5321 || ((ctxt->rep_prefix == REPNE_PREFIX) &&
5322 ((ctxt->eflags & X86_EFLAGS_ZF) == X86_EFLAGS_ZF))))
5323 return true;
5324
5325 return false;
5326}
5327
5328static int flush_pending_x87_faults(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
5329{
5330 int rc;
5331
5332 ctxt->ops->get_fpu(ctxt);
5333 rc = asm_safe("fwait");
5334 ctxt->ops->put_fpu(ctxt);
5335
5336 if (unlikely(rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE))
5337 return emulate_exception(ctxt, MF_VECTOR, 0, false);
5338
5339 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
5340}
5341
5342static void fetch_possible_mmx_operand(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt,
5343 struct operand *op)
5344{
5345 if (op->type == OP_MM)
5346 read_mmx_reg(ctxt, &op->mm_val, op->addr.mm);
5347}
5348
5349static int fastop(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt, void (*fop)(struct fastop *))
5350{
5351 ulong flags = (ctxt->eflags & EFLAGS_MASK) | X86_EFLAGS_IF;
5352
5353 if (!(ctxt->d & ByteOp))
5354 fop += __ffs(ctxt->dst.bytes) * FASTOP_SIZE;
5355
5356 asm("push %[flags]; popf; " CALL_NOSPEC " ; pushf; pop %[flags]\n"
5357 : "+a"(ctxt->dst.val), "+d"(ctxt->src.val), [flags]"+D"(flags),
5358 [thunk_target]"+S"(fop), ASM_CALL_CONSTRAINT
5359 : "c"(ctxt->src2.val));
5360
5361 ctxt->eflags = (ctxt->eflags & ~EFLAGS_MASK) | (flags & EFLAGS_MASK);
5362 if (!fop) /* exception is returned in fop variable */
5363 return emulate_de(ctxt);
5364 return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
5365}
5366
5367void init_decode_cache(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
5368{
5369 memset(&ctxt->rip_relative, 0,
5370 (void *)&ctxt->modrm - (void *)&ctxt->rip_relative);
5371
5372 ctxt->io_read.pos = 0;
5373 ctxt->io_read.end = 0;
5374 ctxt->mem_read.end = 0;
5375}
5376
5377int x86_emulate_insn(struct x86_emulate_ctxt *ctxt)
5378{
5379 const struct x86_emulate_ops *ops = ctxt->ops;
5380 int rc = X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
5381 int saved_dst_type = ctxt->dst.type;
5382 unsigned emul_flags;
5383
5384 ctxt->mem_read.pos = 0;
5385
5386 /* LOCK prefix is allowed only with some instructions */
5387 if (ctxt->lock_prefix && (!(ctxt->d & Lock) || ctxt->dst.type != OP_MEM)) {
5388 rc = emulate_ud(ctxt);
5389 goto done;
5390 }
5391
5392 if ((ctxt->d & SrcMask) == SrcMemFAddr && ctxt->src.type != OP_MEM) {
5393 rc = emulate_ud(ctxt);
5394 goto done;
5395 }
5396
5397 emul_flags = ctxt->ops->get_hflags(ctxt);
5398 if (unlikely(ctxt->d &
5399 (No64|Undefined|Sse|Mmx|Intercept|CheckPerm|Priv|Prot|String))) {
5400 if ((ctxt->mode == X86EMUL_MODE_PROT64 && (ctxt->d & No64)) ||
5401 (ctxt->d & Undefined)) {
5402 rc = emulate_ud(ctxt);
5403 goto done;
5404 }
5405
5406 if (((ctxt->d & (Sse|Mmx)) && ((ops->get_cr(ctxt, 0) & X86_CR0_EM)))
5407 || ((ctxt->d & Sse) && !(ops->get_cr(ctxt, 4) & X86_CR4_OSFXSR))) {
5408 rc = emulate_ud(ctxt);
5409 goto done;
5410 }
5411
5412 if ((ctxt->d & (Sse|Mmx)) && (ops->get_cr(ctxt, 0) & X86_CR0_TS)) {
5413 rc = emulate_nm(ctxt);
5414 goto done;
5415 }
5416
5417 if (ctxt->d & Mmx) {
5418 rc = flush_pending_x87_faults(ctxt);
5419 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5420 goto done;
5421 /*
5422 * Now that we know the fpu is exception safe, we can fetch
5423 * operands from it.
5424 */
5425 fetch_possible_mmx_operand(ctxt, &ctxt->src);
5426 fetch_possible_mmx_operand(ctxt, &ctxt->src2);
5427 if (!(ctxt->d & Mov))
5428 fetch_possible_mmx_operand(ctxt, &ctxt->dst);
5429 }
5430
5431 if (unlikely(emul_flags & X86EMUL_GUEST_MASK) && ctxt->intercept) {
5432 rc = emulator_check_intercept(ctxt, ctxt->intercept,
5433 X86_ICPT_PRE_EXCEPT);
5434 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5435 goto done;
5436 }
5437
5438 /* Instruction can only be executed in protected mode */
5439 if ((ctxt->d & Prot) && ctxt->mode < X86EMUL_MODE_PROT16) {
5440 rc = emulate_ud(ctxt);
5441 goto done;
5442 }
5443
5444 /* Privileged instruction can be executed only in CPL=0 */
5445 if ((ctxt->d & Priv) && ops->cpl(ctxt)) {
5446 if (ctxt->d & PrivUD)
5447 rc = emulate_ud(ctxt);
5448 else
5449 rc = emulate_gp(ctxt, 0);
5450 goto done;
5451 }
5452
5453 /* Do instruction specific permission checks */
5454 if (ctxt->d & CheckPerm) {
5455 rc = ctxt->check_perm(ctxt);
5456 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5457 goto done;
5458 }
5459
5460 if (unlikely(emul_flags & X86EMUL_GUEST_MASK) && (ctxt->d & Intercept)) {
5461 rc = emulator_check_intercept(ctxt, ctxt->intercept,
5462 X86_ICPT_POST_EXCEPT);
5463 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5464 goto done;
5465 }
5466
5467 if (ctxt->rep_prefix && (ctxt->d & String)) {
5468 /* All REP prefixes have the same first termination condition */
5469 if (address_mask(ctxt, reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RCX)) == 0) {
5470 string_registers_quirk(ctxt);
5471 ctxt->eip = ctxt->_eip;
5472 ctxt->eflags &= ~X86_EFLAGS_RF;
5473 goto done;
5474 }
5475 }
5476 }
5477
5478 if ((ctxt->src.type == OP_MEM) && !(ctxt->d & NoAccess)) {
5479 rc = segmented_read(ctxt, ctxt->src.addr.mem,
5480 ctxt->src.valptr, ctxt->src.bytes);
5481 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5482 goto done;
5483 ctxt->src.orig_val64 = ctxt->src.val64;
5484 }
5485
5486 if (ctxt->src2.type == OP_MEM) {
5487 rc = segmented_read(ctxt, ctxt->src2.addr.mem,
5488 &ctxt->src2.val, ctxt->src2.bytes);
5489 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5490 goto done;
5491 }
5492
5493 if ((ctxt->d & DstMask) == ImplicitOps)
5494 goto special_insn;
5495
5496
5497 if ((ctxt->dst.type == OP_MEM) && !(ctxt->d & Mov)) {
5498 /* optimisation - avoid slow emulated read if Mov */
5499 rc = segmented_read(ctxt, ctxt->dst.addr.mem,
5500 &ctxt->dst.val, ctxt->dst.bytes);
5501 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE) {
5502 if (!(ctxt->d & NoWrite) &&
5503 rc == X86EMUL_PROPAGATE_FAULT &&
5504 ctxt->exception.vector == PF_VECTOR)
5505 ctxt->exception.error_code |= PFERR_WRITE_MASK;
5506 goto done;
5507 }
5508 }
5509 /* Copy full 64-bit value for CMPXCHG8B. */
5510 ctxt->dst.orig_val64 = ctxt->dst.val64;
5511
5512special_insn:
5513
5514 if (unlikely(emul_flags & X86EMUL_GUEST_MASK) && (ctxt->d & Intercept)) {
5515 rc = emulator_check_intercept(ctxt, ctxt->intercept,
5516 X86_ICPT_POST_MEMACCESS);
5517 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5518 goto done;
5519 }
5520
5521 if (ctxt->rep_prefix && (ctxt->d & String))
5522 ctxt->eflags |= X86_EFLAGS_RF;
5523 else
5524 ctxt->eflags &= ~X86_EFLAGS_RF;
5525
5526 if (ctxt->execute) {
5527 if (ctxt->d & Fastop) {
5528 void (*fop)(struct fastop *) = (void *)ctxt->execute;
5529 rc = fastop(ctxt, fop);
5530 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5531 goto done;
5532 goto writeback;
5533 }
5534 rc = ctxt->execute(ctxt);
5535 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5536 goto done;
5537 goto writeback;
5538 }
5539
5540 if (ctxt->opcode_len == 2)
5541 goto twobyte_insn;
5542 else if (ctxt->opcode_len == 3)
5543 goto threebyte_insn;
5544
5545 switch (ctxt->b) {
5546 case 0x70 ... 0x7f: /* jcc (short) */
5547 if (test_cc(ctxt->b, ctxt->eflags))
5548 rc = jmp_rel(ctxt, ctxt->src.val);
5549 break;
5550 case 0x8d: /* lea r16/r32, m */
5551 ctxt->dst.val = ctxt->src.addr.mem.ea;
5552 break;
5553 case 0x90 ... 0x97: /* nop / xchg reg, rax */
5554 if (ctxt->dst.addr.reg == reg_rmw(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RAX))
5555 ctxt->dst.type = OP_NONE;
5556 else
5557 rc = em_xchg(ctxt);
5558 break;
5559 case 0x98: /* cbw/cwde/cdqe */
5560 switch (ctxt->op_bytes) {
5561 case 2: ctxt->dst.val = (s8)ctxt->dst.val; break;
5562 case 4: ctxt->dst.val = (s16)ctxt->dst.val; break;
5563 case 8: ctxt->dst.val = (s32)ctxt->dst.val; break;
5564 }
5565 break;
5566 case 0xcc: /* int3 */
5567 rc = emulate_int(ctxt, 3);
5568 break;
5569 case 0xcd: /* int n */
5570 rc = emulate_int(ctxt, ctxt->src.val);
5571 break;
5572 case 0xce: /* into */
5573 if (ctxt->eflags & X86_EFLAGS_OF)
5574 rc = emulate_int(ctxt, 4);
5575 break;
5576 case 0xe9: /* jmp rel */
5577 case 0xeb: /* jmp rel short */
5578 rc = jmp_rel(ctxt, ctxt->src.val);
5579 ctxt->dst.type = OP_NONE; /* Disable writeback. */
5580 break;
5581 case 0xf4: /* hlt */
5582 ctxt->ops->halt(ctxt);
5583 break;
5584 case 0xf5: /* cmc */
5585 /* complement carry flag from eflags reg */
5586 ctxt->eflags ^= X86_EFLAGS_CF;
5587 break;
5588 case 0xf8: /* clc */
5589 ctxt->eflags &= ~X86_EFLAGS_CF;
5590 break;
5591 case 0xf9: /* stc */
5592 ctxt->eflags |= X86_EFLAGS_CF;
5593 break;
5594 case 0xfc: /* cld */
5595 ctxt->eflags &= ~X86_EFLAGS_DF;
5596 break;
5597 case 0xfd: /* std */
5598 ctxt->eflags |= X86_EFLAGS_DF;
5599 break;
5600 default:
5601 goto cannot_emulate;
5602 }
5603
5604 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5605 goto done;
5606
5607writeback:
5608 if (ctxt->d & SrcWrite) {
5609 BUG_ON(ctxt->src.type == OP_MEM || ctxt->src.type == OP_MEM_STR);
5610 rc = writeback(ctxt, &ctxt->src);
5611 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5612 goto done;
5613 }
5614 if (!(ctxt->d & NoWrite)) {
5615 rc = writeback(ctxt, &ctxt->dst);
5616 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5617 goto done;
5618 }
5619
5620 /*
5621 * restore dst type in case the decoding will be reused
5622 * (happens for string instruction )
5623 */
5624 ctxt->dst.type = saved_dst_type;
5625
5626 if ((ctxt->d & SrcMask) == SrcSI)
5627 string_addr_inc(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RSI, &ctxt->src);
5628
5629 if ((ctxt->d & DstMask) == DstDI)
5630 string_addr_inc(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RDI, &ctxt->dst);
5631
5632 if (ctxt->rep_prefix && (ctxt->d & String)) {
5633 unsigned int count;
5634 struct read_cache *r = &ctxt->io_read;
5635 if ((ctxt->d & SrcMask) == SrcSI)
5636 count = ctxt->src.count;
5637 else
5638 count = ctxt->dst.count;
5639 register_address_increment(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RCX, -count);
5640
5641 if (!string_insn_completed(ctxt)) {
5642 /*
5643 * Re-enter guest when pio read ahead buffer is empty
5644 * or, if it is not used, after each 1024 iteration.
5645 */
5646 if ((r->end != 0 || reg_read(ctxt, VCPU_REGS_RCX) & 0x3ff) &&
5647 (r->end == 0 || r->end != r->pos)) {
5648 /*
5649 * Reset read cache. Usually happens before
5650 * decode, but since instruction is restarted
5651 * we have to do it here.
5652 */
5653 ctxt->mem_read.end = 0;
5654 writeback_registers(ctxt);
5655 return EMULATION_RESTART;
5656 }
5657 goto done; /* skip rip writeback */
5658 }
5659 ctxt->eflags &= ~X86_EFLAGS_RF;
5660 }
5661
5662 ctxt->eip = ctxt->_eip;
5663
5664done:
5665 if (rc == X86EMUL_PROPAGATE_FAULT) {
5666 WARN_ON(ctxt->exception.vector > 0x1f);
5667 ctxt->have_exception = true;
5668 }
5669 if (rc == X86EMUL_INTERCEPTED)
5670 return EMULATION_INTERCEPTED;
5671
5672 if (rc == X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5673 writeback_registers(ctxt);
5674
5675 return (rc == X86EMUL_UNHANDLEABLE) ? EMULATION_FAILED : EMULATION_OK;
5676
5677twobyte_insn:
5678 switch (ctxt->b) {
5679 case 0x09: /* wbinvd */
5680 (ctxt->ops->wbinvd)(ctxt);
5681 break;
5682 case 0x08: /* invd */
5683 case 0x0d: /* GrpP (prefetch) */
5684 case 0x18: /* Grp16 (prefetch/nop) */
5685 case 0x1f: /* nop */
5686 break;
5687 case 0x20: /* mov cr, reg */
5688 ctxt->dst.val = ops->get_cr(ctxt, ctxt->modrm_reg);
5689 break;
5690 case 0x21: /* mov from dr to reg */
5691 ops->get_dr(ctxt, ctxt->modrm_reg, &ctxt->dst.val);
5692 break;
5693 case 0x40 ... 0x4f: /* cmov */
5694 if (test_cc(ctxt->b, ctxt->eflags))
5695 ctxt->dst.val = ctxt->src.val;
5696 else if (ctxt->op_bytes != 4)
5697 ctxt->dst.type = OP_NONE; /* no writeback */
5698 break;
5699 case 0x80 ... 0x8f: /* jnz rel, etc*/
5700 if (test_cc(ctxt->b, ctxt->eflags))
5701 rc = jmp_rel(ctxt, ctxt->src.val);
5702 break;
5703 case 0x90 ... 0x9f: /* setcc r/m8 */
5704 ctxt->dst.val = test_cc(ctxt->b, ctxt->eflags);
5705 break;
5706 case 0xb6 ... 0xb7: /* movzx */
5707 ctxt->dst.bytes = ctxt->op_bytes;
5708 ctxt->dst.val = (ctxt->src.bytes == 1) ? (u8) ctxt->src.val
5709 : (u16) ctxt->src.val;
5710 break;
5711 case 0xbe ... 0xbf: /* movsx */
5712 ctxt->dst.bytes = ctxt->op_bytes;
5713 ctxt->dst.val = (ctxt->src.bytes == 1) ? (s8) ctxt->src.val :
5714 (s16) ctxt->src.val;
5715 break;
5716 default:
5717 goto cannot_emulate;
5718 }
5719
5720threebyte_insn:
5721
5722 if (rc != X86EMUL_CONTINUE)
5723 goto done;
5724
5725 goto writeback;
5726
5727cannot_emulate:
5728 return EMULATION_FAILED;
5729}

5742{

5744 return false;
5745
5746 if (ctxt->d & TwoMemOp)
5747 return false;
5748
5749 return true;
